---
import BlogPost from '$lib/layouts/BlogPost.astro';
export const title = "The best part of Command Code's \"deals\": they aren't Command Code's";
export const date = '2026-06-15';
---

<BlogPost {title} {date}>
  <p>
    <strong>DeepSeek V4 Pro</strong>: "4x usage" ($1.74/3.48/0.0145 → $0.435/0.87/0.003625) is
    upstream:
  </p>
  <blockquote>
    <p>
      <a href="https://x.com/deepseek_ai/status/2057854261699195173">@deepseek_ai on May 22, 2026</a
      >
    </p>
    <p>We are making our discount permanent! 🎉</p>
    <p>Enjoy building with DeepSeek-V4-Pro and bring your innovative ideas to life! 🚀</p>
  </blockquote>
  <p>
    <strong>Nemotron 3 Ultra</strong>: "2.3x usage" ($0.5/2.5/0.15 → $0.37/1.08/0.14) is a result of
    switching providers:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      $0.5/2.5/0.15 was likely <a
        href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260616035228/https://deepinfra.com/nvidia/NVIDIA-Nemotron-3-Ultra-550B-A55B"
        >DeepInfra</a
      >
    </li>
    <li>
      $0.37/1.08/0.14 is likely <a
        href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260616035440/https://www.blackbox.ai/api">Blackbox AI</a
      > - not sure if genuinely self hosted, emailed them for comment on this
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>Qwen 3.7 Max</strong>: "2x usage until June 22" ($2.5/7.5/0.5/3.13 →
    1.25/3.75/0.25/1.56) is upstream:
  </p>
  <blockquote>
    <p>
      <a
        href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260602103905/https://www.alibabacloud.com/en/campaign/qwen-discount?_p_lc=1"
        >Alibaba Cloud</a
      >
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>What does the limited-time 50% discount cover?</strong><br />This promotion offers a
      limited-time 50% discount on the Qwen3.7-Max model. The discount applies exclusively to the
      following four billing items: Input, Output, Explicit Cache Creation, and Explicit Cache Hit.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>When does this promotional pricing end?</strong><br />The promotional pricing is
      effective from the moment of release until June 22, 2026. The exact timing is subject to the
      official information displayed on this page.
    </p>
  </blockquote>
  <p>
    <strong>MiniMax M3</strong>: "2x usage" ($0.6/2.4/0.12 → $0.3/1.2/0.06) is upstream: <a
      href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260616040724/https://platform.minimax.io/docs/guides/pricing-paygo.md"
      >"Permanent 50% off"</a
    >
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>MiMo V2.5 Pro and Mimo V2.5</strong>: "Up to 99% off" ($2/6/0.4 → $0.435/0.87/0.0036 +
    $0.8/4/0.16 → $0.14/0.28/0.0028) is upstream: <a
      href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260616040107/https://mimo.mi.com/docs/en-US/news/latest/v2.5-price-update"
      >"Compared to the original API pricing, the new pricing can have a maximum reduction of up to
      99%"</a
    >
  </p>
  <p>
    <em
      >View Command Code's deals page as of writing <a
        href="https://web.archive.org/web/20260616035422/https://commandcode.ai/docs/resources/pricing-limits"
        >here</a
      >. <a href="https://x.com/MrAhmadAwais">Ahmad Awais</a>, Command Code's CEO, currently defends
      this as lower than other model gateways like OpenCode Go (prices locked due to a ZDR
      contract), Nous Portal (no reply), and Kilo (prices via OpenRouter but pessimistic).</em
    >
  </p>
</BlogPost>

<style>
  blockquote {
    quotes: none;
  }
</style>
